cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with estimating pose and shape from RGB images using a Convolutional Neural Network. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper mentions prior work on estimating hand pose and configuration, which is relevant to robotics applications. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper uses machine learning techniques to train the HOPS-Net model. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper focuses on developing a neural network for pose and shape estimation. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses an image-to-image translation model to generate realistically textured objects.
